content: So far so good! Saw lots of people say pics won't save, unsupported file, mine did as well, but still saved. Having lots of fun, would be nice if the developer dis an update tho, apparently it's been years. 4 out of 5!
Love this app! Used it for year's

Great app! But... A feature I would love to see is a blade clash effect. Like, a white explosion that you could change the size of for the sabers. Also, for some reason it saves images upside down, and it's a hassle to reconfigure them. But aside from that, it's just what I needed. And I don't know if anyone would need this, but something else that would be nice to have is a swooshing effect.
Definitely not worth 99 cents.
This app would have been cool but unfortunately it decreases the quality of your image pretty drastically. If it didn't do that I would have given it five stars...very disappointing...
Darn shame. Files won't save.
It does what it says on the tin. However it won't save images once edited. It's says "file unsupported"
Amazing app. Cheap and effective. Does exactly what it says on the tin. Recommended and shared!
Its amazing and cheap and its easy! And the best part is that the effects are off the hook!!! :)
Perfect! I have been looking for an app to add lightsaber effects to my pics and first try out, it worked!
Won't save photos!!! Please fix that!!!
Easy to use and finished photo looks great
Unsupported file when trying to save
easy to use, works well on my photos
Downgrades the quality of the photo you are editing.
unsupported file. please help.
it won't save any of my photos.
It worked perfectly (or at least nearly perfect) until my damn phone software updated... now it won't save and keeps saying unsupported file which is complete bs! FIX IT NOW!
Im on a Samsung S10 plus and refunded because it won't save the photos due to it being an unsupported file.. Shame, it is a pretty cool app had it worked.
I love this App
Will not save any picture. "unsupported file" every time I try to save.

Works pretty good. If you see pixels, that's because your not creating a straight line. Otherwise that will happen. This works perfectly for my needs. Very happy with it. Sadly, this app is no longer being supported. The ladt update was nearly 3 years ago...
Almost perfect! Just need a feature to add hilts to the photos.
great app for collectors who wish to bring their figures to life
Amzing for photos of figures that need that lightsaber and blaster touch.
Nice simple effective
The quality of the saber after we put on the photo ia pixalete. Not very good quality at the end.
Fantastic! Can add any angle and color to any photo. Absolutely recommend.
Does what I want it to.. Action figures with saber effects.. Glorious.
Good i guess
...a more civilised era.

Despite reviews that say no photo quality lost, that is not the case. Also, sabers pixelate and segment when placed at any any angle. Access to full color spectrum and multiple sabers is great, though.
Bought the app for my Xperia and it won't let me save a finished photo. A tad frustrating as it's such a good app!
The best on the play store

For me this is the best lightsaber effects photo editor app you'll find currently. No loss of image quality like most others and it's easy to use offering good selection of colours. Only one negative is sometimes if angling lightsaber in a certain direction the lines goes rather fuzzy/ pixelated. There is definitely potential for making this app even better; Kylo Ren type saber and potentially adding other effects such as; laser blaster bolts. I would definitely recommend this app to all Star Wars fans!
Exactly what I wanted. No more loss of image quality.
2 recommendations: add blaster bolts and optional hilts
So easy to use! I would recommend this to anyone looking to add light sabers to pics of wildlife, aquatic mammals, and on occasion, amphibians.
